article.headline: Lilly scores 25, Brown defeats Pennsylvania 71-64
article.description: — Kino Lilly Jr.'s 25 points helped Brown defeat Pennsylvania 71-64 on Saturday night.
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Kino Lilly Jr.'s 25 points helped Brown defeat Pennsylvania 71-64 on Saturday night. Lilly was 5 of 16 shooting, including 3 for 8 from 3-point range, and went 12 for 12 from the line for the Bears (7-17, 3-6 Ivy League). AJ Lesburt Jr. scored 11 points while shooting 4 for 9, including 3 for 8 from beyond the arc, and added six rebounds. Kimo Ferrari had 11 points and shot 4 for 5, including 3 for 4 from beyond the arc. Clark Slajchert led the Quakers (9-15, 1-8) in scoring, finishing with 32 points. Nick Spinoso added eight points, nine rebounds, four assists and two steals for Pennsylvania. In addition, Tyler Perkins had seven points. The loss was the Quakers' eighth straight. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
